ians", "commercial streets", "alaska", "photographic prints", "city & town life", "united states"], "timestamp": "2022-11-29T20:00:20.351Z", "title": "Street scene", "type": ["still image"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/99614944/"}], "resource": {"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/ak/batch_ak_dolphin_ver01/data/sn84020665/00514154880/1948081001/0543.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ak:batch_ak_dolphin_ver01:data:sn84020665:00514154880:1948081001:0543/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/ak/batch_ak_dolphin_ver01/data/sn84020665/00514154880/1948081001/0543.pdf", "segment_count": 4, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84020665/1948-08-10/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}, "resources": [{"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/ak/batch_ak_dolphin_ver01/data/sn84020665/00514154880/1948081001/0543.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ak:batch_ak_dolphin_ver01:data:sn84020665:00514154880:1948081001:0543/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/ak/batch_ak_dolphin_ver01/data/sn84020665/00514154880/1948081001/0543.pdf", "segment_count": 4, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84020665/1948-08-10/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/ak/batch_ak_dolphin_ver01/data/sn84020665/00514154880/1948081001/0543.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84020665/1948-08-10/ed-1/?sp=1"], "batch": ["ak_dolphin_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/alaska/", "3/united states/alaska/palmer/"], "contributor": ["alaska state library historical collections"], "date": "1948-08-10", "dates": ["1948-08-10"], "description": ["Vol 1 No 86 Palmer Alaska August 10 1948 Ten Cents The annual spilling of the waters of Lake George is pictured in these scenes The event which took place during the Pas week each year swells the waters of Knik River many feet above its normal level The river is fed by the lake which lies at the face of Knik Glacier During 51 weeks of the year the lake is icelocked at its mouth but during the annual breakup the waters channel their way through the glacier ice which blocks their exit and rush through narrow gorges and over rapids a uPPer reahes of Knik River The photo to the left is an aerial view of the icelocked river channel The broad expanse of Knik Glacier is visible in the picture to the right with the ice capped waters of Lake George lying before it The broad black strip winding down the glacier is a moraine or mound of debris which is pushed ahead of an advancing glacier In this instance the strip marks the meeting place of two glaciers Photos by Palmer Photographic Center Warne Plans Valley Visit William E Warne assistant secretary of 1he interior will"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2024-05-22T12:58:13.907Z", "group": ["ndnp/ak", "alaska-state-library-historical-collections-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84020665/1948-08-10/ed-1/?sp=1", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ak:batch_ak_dolphin_ver01:data:sn84020665:00514154880:1948081001:0543/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=353&w=232", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ak:batch_ak_dolphin_ver01:data:sn84020665:00514154880:1948081001:0543/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=706&w=465", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/ak/batch_ak_dolphin_ver01/data/sn84020665/00514154880/1948081001/0543.xml&format=alto_xml"], "index": 1, "language": ["english"], "locat